United State President Donald Trump has left South Korea after a trip to Asia where he met with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un in the Demilitarized Zone dividing the peninsula. In a tweet, Trump wrote “Leaving South Korea after a wonderful meeting with Chairman Kim Jong Un. Stood on the soil of North Korea, an important statement for all, and a great honor!” Leaving South Korea after a wonderful meeting with Chairman Kim Jong Un. Stood on the soil of North Korea, an important statement for all, and a great honor! — Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) June 30, 2019 